<HEADLINE> Mad Cow Disease Detected in Denmark </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, February 28 (Xinhua) -- A case of mad cow disease
was detected in northern Denmark, the Ministry of Food and
Agriculture said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The cow, in a herd in the north of the Jutland Peninsula, has
been slaughtered and the herd were placed under strict observation.
</P>
<P>
Denmark detected its first case of mad cow disease in August
1992 in a cow imported from Britain. 
</P>
</TEXT>
