<DATE_TIME> 2000-02-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mongolia Negotiates With Russia About Debt Issues </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, February 28 (Xinhua) -- Mongolian delegates
concluded negotiations Monday with Russian counterparts regarding
the debt of 19.75 million U.S. dollars to be paid by Mongolia to
Russia in the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
Delegates from the Mongolian Finance Ministry, the Bank of
Mongolia and the Ministry of External Relations, together with
representatives of the Russian ministries of finance and commerce
and Russian "Vnesheconom" bank took part in the negotiation.
</P>
<P>
The debt is connected with a loan taken by Mongolia from Russia
in 1991-1992.
</P>
<P>
At the talks, the Russian side accepted a proposal of
Mongolians to pay part of the loan by products. Finally, the two
sides reached agreement on paying 6.1 million dollars of the debt
by products in 2000, and the rest of the debt to be paid back
within the following years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
