<HEADLINE> Vietnamese FM to Visit Laos, Cambodia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, February 28 (Xinhua) -- Vietnamese Foreign Minister
Nguyen Dy Nien will pay official visits to Laos and Cambodia
beginning Tuesday, a Vietnamese Foreign Ministry spokeswoman said
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The purpose of Nien's visits are to strengthen the traditional
friendly relations of cooperation between Vietnam and these
countries, the spokeswoman said.
</P>
<P>
During his visit to Laos from February 29 to March 1, the new
Vietnamese foreign minister will meet Chairman of the Lao People's
Revolutionary Party and Lao State President Khamtay Siphandone and
Prime Minister Sisavath Keobounphanh, and will have talks with Lao
Deputy Prime Minister and Foreign Minister Somsavat Lengsavad.
</P>
<P>
While in Cambodia on March 3-5, Nien will meet Cambodia's
acting head of state Chea Sim, Prime Minister Hun Sen, and
National Assembly President Norodom Ranariddh and will have talks
with Minister of Foreign Affairs and International Cooperation Hor
Nam Hong.
</P>
<P>
These talks will focus on bilateral relations and regional and
international issues of common concern.
</P>
<P>
Nien assumed the post of foreign minister in January. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
