<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India, Singapore Launch Joint Naval Exercise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, February 28 (Xinhua) -- Indian and Singaporean naval
forces began on Monday an 11-day anti-submarine warfare joint
exercise in the Andaman Seas off Port Blair of India, the Press
Trust of India (PTI) reported.
</P>
<P>
Two frigates and a submarine of the Indian navy are taking part
in the exercise, while Singapore has sent two missile corvettes
and two anti-submarine patrol ships, said the PTI.
</P>
<P>
The exercise is aimed at promoting inter-operability and
understanding of operational methods of the two navies, the PTI
quoted an Indian navy spokesman as saying.
</P>
<P>
Navy officials from both sides started mutual briefings shortly
after the Singaporean ships arrived at Port Blair on Monday
morning, and the navies would be out in the sea very soon, the
spokesman added.
</P>
<P>
This is the seventh exercise of its kind between the navies of
the two nations since 1993, the PTI said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
