<HEADLINE> Europe's Main Stocks Close Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, February 29 (Xinhua) -- Europe's main stocks closed
firmly ahead Tuesday as energy, financial and auto stocks powered
their indexes higher.
</P>
<P>
London's benchmark FTSE 100 index was Europe's best performer,
closing up 133 points, or 2.2 percent, at of 6,232.60, lifted by
sharp gains in its two heavyweight oil and gas components, BP
Amoco and Shell Transport &AMP;Trading.
</P>
<P>
