7,644.55, with its auto components moving strongly ahead following
recent strong earnings announcements.
</P>
<P>
In Paris, the CAC 40 index closed up 88 points, or 1.45 percent,
at 6,190.96, boosted by a double-digit rise in technology
consulting firm Cap Gemini after it acquired the management
consultancy practice of Ernst &AMP; Young. 
