<DATE_TIME> 2000-02-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Security Council Renews U.N. Mission in Western Sahara </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, February 29 (Xinhua) -- The U.N. Security
Council Tuesday unanimously adopted a resolution to extend the
mandate of the United Nations Mission for a Referendum in the
Western Sahara (MINURSO) until May 31.
</P>
<P>
The extension was seen as the continued U.N. efforts to
implement the Settlement Plan and agreements adopted by the
parties to hold a free, fair and impartial referendum for the self-
determination of the people of the Western Sahara.
</P>
<P>
The resolution supports the intention of U.N. Secretary-
General Kofi Annan to ask his special envoy to consult the parties
and, taking into account "existing and potential obstacles," to
explore ways and means to achieve an early, durable and agreed
resolution of their dispute, which is characterized by who can
vote in the proposed referendum and concerns that the results
might never be implemented.
</P>
<P>
In a remarkable blunt report on February 19, Annan said that
the "fundamental differences" between Morocco and rebels over a
voter registration list had again destroyed the timetable for the
referendum and made it impossible to set a new date.
</P>
<P>
Disagreements over such a core issue "could eventually prevent
the holding of the referendum as provided by the plan," Annan said.
</P>
<P>
War broke out in the Western Sahara in 1976 after Spain
withdrew from the Atlantic coast territory and Morocco annexed it
and moved in settlers. The fighting, which pitted 15,000 ragtag
guerrilla fighters from the rebel Polisario Front against Morocco'
s U.S.-equipped army, ended with a 1991 U.N.-negotiated cease-fire.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations then launched a plan to hold a referendum
to decide whether residents of the mineral-rich northern African
territory would become independent or part of Morocco.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations has been working since 1991 to identify
voters because of disagreements over who is eligible to cast
ballots. 
</P>
