<HEADLINE> U.N.: Prolonged War Boasts Illicit Opium Production in Afghanistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The provinces of Helmand and Nangarhar remained the two
dominant areas for opium poppy cultivation, representing
respectively 49 percent and 26 percent of total areas under
cultivation, and in 1998/1999, opium cultivation has also spread
to new areas, especially in northern and north-eastern Afghanistan,
the report said.
</P>
<P>
The increase in the production of illicit raw opium was even
more dramatic than the increase in the areas under cultivation:
total output of raw opium is estimated to have jumped from 2,700
metric tons in 1998 to 4,600 metric tons in 1999, a staggering
annual increase of 70 percent, according to the report.
</P>
<P>
Ideal weather conditions during 1999 were the main reason that
the increase of opium production exceeded that of cultivation, the
report said. 
</P>
