participating in the NATO-led multinational peacekeeping force in
Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
Greek Defense Minister Akis Tsohatzopoulos has characterized
the Greek force in Kosovo as adequate and very effective. He also
noted that no additional Greek soldiers will be sent to Kosovo,
which has seen in recent days rising violence between French
peacekeepers and ethnic Albanians.
</P>
<P>
