<HEADLINE> World Bank Has Projects in Pipeline Worth $100M for Rwanda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, February 29 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank has four
projects worth over 100 million U.S. dollars in pipeline for
Rwanda, the Rwanda News Agency reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Two of them are specifically designed for the rural areas,
according to the World Bank country office in the Rwandan capital
Kigali.
</P>
<P>
The Rwandan rural areas are to benefit from the rural water
supply project worth 15 million dollars, and the rural sector
support project worth 15 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
The human resources development project worth 35 million
dollars is in the advanced stages and is scheduled to be presented
to the World Bank headquarters in May this year.
</P>
<P>
With a vote of funding worth 40 million dollars, the World Bank
also gave great attention to the development of the private sector
in Rwanda.
</P>
<P>
All these projects are to run for a two-year period, expiring
in the year 2001 when another country assistance strategy will be
drawn and laid for Rwanda by the World Bank. 
</P>
</TEXT>
