<HEADLINE> Iran Reaffirms Support for Lebanese Resistance Movement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, February 29 (Xinhua) -- Iran on Tuesday reiterates its
support for Lebanon's independence, territorial integrity and
national unity as well as the Lebanese resistance movement fighting
against Israeli occupation.
</P>
<P>
Iranian Majlis (Parliament) Speaker Ali Akbar Nateq Nouri and
former President Hashemi Rafsanjani all made clear Tehran's stance
during their separate meetings with visiting President of the
Lebanese National Assembly Nabin Berri.
</P>
<P>
Nouri said that solidarity and cohesion among the Lebanese
nation and the brave stances taken by Lebanese officials in support
of Lebanese resistance movement against the Israeli expansionist
policies are the sole way of repelling Israeli aggression.
</P>
<P>
He also voiced Tehran's readiness to contribute to Lebanon's
reconstruction and help repair civilian installations damaged in
the Israeli air raids, the Islamic Republic News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Iran has a religious and nationalistic attitudes towards
Lebanese and Palestinian issues and all Iranian officials are of
the belief that the present policy on the issues should be followed
vigorously, Nouri assured his Lebanese counterpart.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Rafsanjani, who is the current chairman of the
arbitral and advisory State Expediency Council, lauded the position
of the Lebanese people and government in supporting the Lebanese
resistance movement against Israel.
</P>
<P>
Iran continues its support for the movement, he said, expressing
hoped for peace, tranquility and stability in Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
Refusing to recognize the Jewish regime, Iran has allegedly
supplied arms to the Lebanese Hezbollah guerrillas in their
fighting to end Israeli occupation. But Tehran always denied the
allegation.
</P>
<P>
Both Nouri and Rafsanjani also called for expanding cooperation
in political, cultural, economic and parliamentary fields between
Iran and Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
Berri, who arrived here Sunday night, thanked Iran for its
principled stances towards Lebanese and Palestinian issues, calling
for expansion of mutual cooperation, especially between the two
countries' parliaments.
</P>
<P>
Briefing Iranian officials on the latest political, military and
social developments in Lebanon, he said that his country is
determined to continue resistance and consolidate its relations
with its friends in a bid to effectively confront the expansionist
policies of the Israeli regime. 
</P>
</TEXT>
