<HEADLINE> China to Build National Health Info Network </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 29 (Xinhua) -- China's Ministry of Health (
MOH) plans to build a national computer-based network to improve
its ability of monitor epidemics and control disease.
</P>
<P>
The National Health Information Network, adopting Internet
technology and satellite communications, will connect the MOH
headquarters with provincial and city-level departments of health.
</P>
<P>
After the construction, which may take about two years, the
reports of epidemic situations to the MOH will be accelerated to
enable disease control departments to take prompt action,
according to specialists with the MOH's Statistics and Information
Center. 
</P>
