<DOCNO> XIE20000229.0071 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-02-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Full-Scale Military Operation in Chechnya Ends: Russian Military </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, February 29 (Xinhua) -- Russian troops Tuesday took the
town of Shatoi of the breakaway republic of Chechnya, the last
stronghold held by the rebels in the southern mountains, said the
Russian military.
</P>
<P>
Fighting for the administrative center of the Shatoi District,
situated in the center of the Argun gorge at the foothills of the
southern mountains, began in mid-February. Some 3,000 militants
were defending Shatoi in order to hold it for a long time as the
last fortress for reviving separatism.
</P>
<P>
The seizure of Shatoi made it possible for Russian troops to
remove the blockade of the Argun valley and to start clean-up
operations in the mountains, and Moscow regarded it as the end of
the large-scale military operation in Chechnya, said head of the
Russian Joint Forces in the North Caucasus.
</P>
<P>
In a Tuesday interview with the Russian NTV television company,
Acting Commander of the joint forces Colonel General Gennadi
Troshev said Shatoi and other nine populated localities in the
Argun valley have been under full control of the federal troops.
</P>
<P>
He said in the coming weeks the federal units will chase and
destroy small rebel groups who are trying to break through the
encirclement.
</P>
<P>
He assured that the federal troops won't withdraw from the
highland areas of Chechnya. "They will stage clean-up operations
in populated settlements, combing villages, forests, mountains and
gorges as many times as it is necessary," he said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the headquarters of the Russian federal forces in
the Northern Caucasus said that Chechen rebel leaders, including "
Chechen President" Aslan Maskhadov and rebel field commanders
Shamil Basayev and Salman Raduyev, have escaped from Shatoi into
the mountains. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
