<HEADLINE> China Initiates Bird Protection Campaign </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, February 29 (Xinhua) -- An annual campaign to raise
public awareness for the need to protect birds was initiated today
near east China's Poyang Lake nature reserve, a major habitat of
migratory birds of the country.
</P>
<P>
The week-long bird-lovers activity has been held for 19 years,
however, China has not thoroughly wiped out illegal poaching and
trading of birds, acknowledged a Chinese official in charge of
wildlife protection.
</P>
<P>
"Some offenders still shoot wild birds to sell to restaurants,"
said Wang Fuxing, secretary-general of the Chinese Association for
Wildlife Protection. But he also stressed that the illegal
practice has been curbed since the State Forestry Administration
issued an urgent order asking for more vigilant protection.
</P>
<P>
In the Poyang Lake area, crackdowns upon bird poaching are
underway since shootings of swans were revealed and triggered the
concern of the government of Jiangxi Province late last year.
