<HEADLINE> Malaysia Airlines Returns in Black </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, February 29 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian Airline System
Bhd (MAS) has returned in the black with a pre-tax profit for the
nine months by December 31, 1999 after suffering a pre-tax loss in
the same period in 1998, the company said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
During the period under review, the pre-tax profit amounted to
60.95 million ringgit (16.039 million U.S. dollars) against a pre-
tax loss of 702.66 million ringgit (184.91 million U.S. dollars),
it said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
The company statement said the group turnover grew 10 percent
to 5.942 billion ringgit (1.563 billion U.S. dollars) during the
period from 5.401 billion ringgit (1.421 billion U.S. dollars)
previously, it said.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia Airlines said that during the period, the capacity
expanded 11.4 percent to 5,532.3 million ton kilometers while
traffic grew 16 percent to 3,508.9 million ton kilometers.
</P>
<P>
The overall load factor improved 2.5 percent for the period to
63.4 percent with passenger and cargo load factors to 70.6 percent
and 53.6 percent respectively, it said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
