<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Euro Zone Annual Inflation Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, February 29 (Xinhua) -- The annual inflation rate for
the 11-nation euro zone went from 1.7 percent last December to 2.0
percent in January of this year, Eurostat reported on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Luxembourg-based statistical bureau of the European
community said that the inflation rate was 0.8 percent for the 11
countries in the same period of the previous year.
</P>
<P>
In January, the annual inflation rate for the 15-nation
European Union (EU) also went up, from 1.7 percent last December
to 1.8 percent, compared with 1.0 percent 12 months ago.
</P>
<P>
Ireland posted the highest inflation rate of 4.4 percent among
the EU member states while Britain registered the lowest inflation
rate of 0.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
The EU recommends that the annual inflation rate for member
states be kept at 1.5 percent to be fit for its economic and
monetary union. 
</P>
</TEXT>
