<HEADLINE> Some 760,000 Smuggled CDs Seized in Guangdong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, February 29 (Xinhua) -- Customs officers in south
China's Guangdong Province seized 760,000 compact disks in an
effort to curb smuggling of the cargo from overseas into the
Chinese mainland via the sea.
</P>
<P>
The confiscated cds were found to be pirated publications or be
pornographic and were seized in five major smuggling cases dealt
with on the sea in the first 40 days of the year.
</P>
<P>
Smuggling cds from overseas into the mainland via the sea has
been serious in the past months, so, customs officers of Guangdong
stepped up cooperation with customs officers of Hong Kong and
intensified monitoring larger marine transport tools. The efforts
proved effective.
</P>
<P>
Customs officers of Hong Kong recently also dealt with three
attempted cases to smuggle cds into the mainland via the sea and
confiscated 1.15 million cds from the operations. 
</P>
