<HEADLINE> Chinese, Israeli Trade Ministers Co-Chair Committee Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 29 (Xinhua)-- Shi Guangsheng, China's
Minister of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation (MOFTEC), met
here today with an Israeli delegation headed by Ran Cohen, Israeli
Minister of Industry and Trade, and the two co-chaired the 3rd
Conference of China-Israel Mixed Committee on Trade and Economic
Cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Trade and economic ties between China and Israel have seen
sound and speedy development since the two countries established
diplomatic relations eight years ago, thanks to efforts by both
governments and leaders of the two states as well as businesses in
the two countries, Shi noted.
</P>
<P>
Cooperation in areas of trade, technology, investment and labor
service has maintained stable growth, Shi said. He hoped that
businesses of the two countries would explore more ways to expand
the range of bilateral trade and investment, scientific
cooperation and labor service cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Cohen said that Israel has been interested in expanding trade
relations with China, adding that a major task of his Chinese tour
is to strengthen existing trade links.
</P>
<P>
Cohen stressed that Israel firmly supports China's bid to enter
the World Trade Organization.
</P>
<P>
During the 3rd Conference of the China-Israel Mixed Committee
on Trade and Economic Cooperation, discussions will be held on
three separate areas, agriculture, medicine and medical science,
and the information industry, to pave the way for future joint
work, according to MOFTEC officials. 
