<HEADLINE> Australia Plans to Export Bamboo Shoots to Asia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, February 29 (Xinhua) "Supplying bamboo shoots to Asia?
At first glance it may seem like supplying coal to Newcastle." It
is a lead of a report of AAP Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Newcastle is a city in New South Wales state of Australia and
famous as a coal mine.
</P>
<P>
According to the report ,a man named as Victor Cusack formed
his Bamboo Plantations of Australia Ltd (BPA) and planned to raise
35.58 million U.S. dollars to establish the first large commercial
bamboo plantation in the Southern Hemisphere and supply fresh
bamboo shoots out of season to Asian, American, Canadian and
European, as well as Australian markets.
</P>
<P>
Around 40 percent of the world's population consume edible
bamboo shoots, Cusack said, adding that currently in Asia,
consumers paid high prices for fresh shoots out of season and
resorted to tinned shoots or dried shoots as a substitute.
</P>
<P>
"Prices for fresh shoots are going up to around 62 U.S. cents a
kilo and we can supply at prices the same as or less than that,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
In the United States, people consumed around 35,000 tonnes and
in Australia around 8,000 tonnes, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
