<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sick Siberian Tiger Regains Appetite </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, February 29 (Xinhua) -- Meimei, the sick female
Siberian tiger who fell ill after eating poisonous meat, has
regained her appetite, zoo-keepers say.
</P>
<P>
Last Friday morning when she first regained appetite, she ate
one kilo of fresh beef and drank two kilos of water after being
hospitalized for two weeks.
</P>
<P>
Li Jianhua, the zoo-keeper at the Shenyang Zoo, said that "
Meimei's recovery is just a miracle." However, this doesn't mean
that Meimei is out of danger. Vets are keeping a close eye on the
tiger.
</P>
<P>
Meimei's medical record shows that she has been suffering from
stomach problems over the past two years. The poisonous meat was
the last straw.
</P>
<P>
Poisonous frozen meat caused two female tigers, Duoduo and
Meimei, to contract food poisoning on February 10. Duoduo died
and Meimei went into a coma.
</P>
<P>
Meimei was an present from the U.S. government. Since the late
1980s, she has given birth to ten tiger cubs.
</P>
<P>
Siberian tigers are among the top ten most endangered species
in the world. There are only around 300 remaining in the wild. The
Shenyang Zoo has bred and raised 13 Siberian tigers. One of the
tigers had a cesarean which attracted nationwide publicity.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
