<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chengdu Simplifies Exit and Entry Procedures </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, February 29 (Xinhua) -- The Public Security Bureau of
Chengdu, capital of southwest China's Sichuan Province, recently
simplified its exit and entry procedures as part of the measures
to speed up economic growth in western China.
</P>
<P>
Chinese citizens who are going abroad from Chengdu need only
show their valid exit-entry certificates or visa. In-coming
foreign investors and Taiwan compatriots who are on business trips
will be allowed to enter and go through required procedures
afterward.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the local government has put an end to the old
practice of asking for flight schedules from aviation companies in
countries granting visa-free access to China. They may go through
entry-exit procedures after the border inspection department
affixes the seal to the contract.
</P>
<P>
Shuangliu Airport in Chengdu, the largest international airport
in western China, has handled 20,000 aircraft with 1.6 million
Chinese and overseas passengers since 1990.
</P>
<P>
Reform of existing customs inspection management and
simplification of customs procedures will help improve efficiency
and attract more investors to western part of China, said a local
customs official.  
</P>
</TEXT>
