<HEADLINE> Power Company to Aid Experiments on Coral Reefs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, February 29 (Xinhua) -- Luneng Conglomerate, a power
giant from east China's Shandong Province, will pump up a big sum
of money in supporting experiments on coral reefs at south China's
Sanya Coral Reefs Nature Reserve in Hainan Province.
</P>
<P>
The move is aimed to find out scientific methods to improve the
ecological environment in the offshore areas of China.
</P>
<P>
The experiments will include transplantation, cultivation and
regeneration of coral reefs, according to an agreement signed
between the company and Sanya Coral Reefs Nature Reserve recently.
</P>
<P>
Sanya Coral Reefs Nature Reserve, founded on September 30, 1990,
is the only state-level maritime nature reserve designed to
protect ecological system of corals, coral reefs and marine bio-
diversity.
</P>
<P>
It consists of three parts and gives protection to 56 sq km of
offshore areas. Inside the nature reserve, there are 115 kinds of
proven corals. The nature reserve has become a must-visit item
among tourists to Sanya, which sits on the southern tip of Hainan
Island.  
</P>
