<HEADLINE> Infrastructure Construction at Tianjin Port Attracts International Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, February 29 (Xinhua) -- North China's Tianjin Port
will carry out construction of a number of infrastructural
projects this year.
</P>
<P>
The new projects have already attracted the interest of
multinationals and become the focus of investment by them, said
local sources.
</P>
<P>
According to local sources, seven 10,000 dwt docks will be
constructed at Tianjin Port this year.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, eight other existing container wharves will
also be rebuilt, coupled with the construction of a number of ship
locks.
</P>
<P>
Multinationals based in the United States, Britain and the
Netherlands recently sent their representatives to Tianjin to
negotiate matters relating to investing in construction of coal
docks at Nanjiang Port Area of Tianjin Port and reconstruction of
three container berths at Beijiang Port Area.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin is one of the earliest ports opened to the outside
world and is one of the first group of places to have
international capital.
</P>
<P>
So far, 43 Sino-foreign joint ventures have been set up in
Tianjin Port. These joint ventures are engaged in dock
construction and operation, transportation of containers, cargo
loading and unloading, product packaging and storage, as well as
repairs of machinery.
</P>
<P>
Overseas investment of 280 million U.S. dollars has been placed
into Tianjin Port, of which, 53.34 million U.S. dollars was
invested directly in last year alone.  
