<HEADLINE> Price of Industrial Goods Rises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 29 (Xinhua) -- Figures from the National
Bureau of Statistics (NBS) released today show that the purchasing
price of raw materials, fuel and power rose 2.1 percent in January
from the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Sales of industrial goods improved as selling prices remained
stable comparing with last year.
</P>
<P>
Areas in north and west China, including major industrial bases
such as Tianjin, Liaoning, Jilin, Heilongjiang and Chongqing and
raw material producers such as Gansu, Qinghai, Ningxia and
Xinjiang saw the biggest price increases in January.
</P>
<P>
The NBS said the increase in the prices of mining products,
especially oil, is the main factor in the price hike of industrial
goods. The price of mining products rose 18.7 percent in January.
</P>
<P>
Due to the rising prices of crude oil on the international
market, the price of petroleum products in China jumped by 30.3
percent in January.
</P>
<P>
Prices of electricity, textile, non-ferrous metallurgy and
building materials also rose considerably this month.  
</P>
</TEXT>
