<HEADLINE> Malaysia's Asset Management Company Issues More Bonds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, February 29 (Xinhua) -- Pengurusan Danaharta
Nasional Bhd, Malaysia's national asset management company set up
to acquire non-performing loans (NPLs), Tuesday issued bonds of
305.1 million ringgit (80.289 million U.S. dollars) in nominal
value under its bonds issuance program.
</P>
<P>
These bonds, which will mature on March 31, 2005, are the
second tranche issued under the sixth series of the program,
Danaharta said.
</P>
<P>
The bonds were issued to eight financial institutions as
consideration for NPLs purchased by Danaharta which has been
buying NPLs in efforts to clean up the balance sheet of banks
facing financial difficulties due to the economic recession.
</P>
<P>
The company has to date issued bonds of a total amount of 10.
812 billion ringgit (2.845 billion U.S. dollars) in nominal value.
</P>
<P>
Under its bonds issuance program, Danaharta will issue up to 15
billion ringgit (3.947 billion U.S. dollars) in nominal value of
government guaranteed zero coupons redeemable bonds.
</P>
<P>
These bonds are issued progressively, the timing and size of
which are in line with Danaharta's acquisition process.
</P>
<P>
Danaharta has the option of refinancing any of the bond upon
maturity for an additional period of one year, three years and
five years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
