<BODY>
<HEADLINE> About 2300 Deserters Return to Sri Lankan Army </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The amnesty from February 21 to 27 was a response to appeals
made to the army commander by many deserters and their parents.
</P>
<P>
All of them will be re-equipped and given a eight-week
refresher course before they join their former battalion. They
will be paid their former salaries from the day they reported back
and they will serve in the same rank in at the time of their
desertion but will lose their seniority, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
These deserters returned to their army will receive no
punishment except in exceptional cases if they are wanted by the
police for any criminal offense during their desertion period, the
sources added.
</P>
<P>
The Sri Lankan government have launched many times of the
amnesty since 1995. Many of deserters reportedly returned to the
army. However, there are still thousands army deserters who failed
to respond to the amnesty. 
</P>
</TEXT>
