The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) edged up 1.85 points to
end at 2,120.50 points.
</P>
<P>
The turnover increased to 663.47 million units valued at 773.67
million Singapore dollars (449.99 million U.S. dollars). Losers
outpaced gainers by 231 to 109 with 172 counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Uraco was the most active stock with a volume of 93.16 million
units. IPC was the second most heavily traded stock with a
turnover of 86.35 million shares. Innop was the next with 34.46
million counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
Venture was the top gainer of the day surging up 90 cents to
close at 25.90 Singapore dollars. SPH climbed up by 80 cents to
finish at 33.00 Singapore dollars. SPH 100 rose by 50 cents to end
at 32.90 Singapore dollars.
</P>
