On the downside, Creative 50 topped losers of the day as it
incurred a loss of 50 cents to end at 37.50 Singapore dollars.
Both OCBC and UOB shed 40 cents to finish at 10.90 Singapore
dollars. Chartered and NatElec retreated 30 cents to close at 14.
70 and 10.70 Singapore dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said that there were few new leads to move investors.
But the market managed to find some support from gains in several
blue-chip counters.
</P>
<P>
They noted SingTel ended higher despite the group losing its
bid for Cable &AMP; Wireless HKT. 
