<P>
HONG KONG, February 29 (Xinhua) -- The gold price in Hong Kong
went up eight HK dollars to close at 2,720 a tael Tuesday,
according to Po Sang Bank, one of the major gold dealers in Hong
Kong.
</P>
<P>
The gold price is equivalent to 293.40 U.S. dollars a troy
ounce, 0.87 U.S. dollars down from the previous close, at Tuesday'
s exchange rate of one U.S. dollar against 7.7820 HK dollars.
</P>
