<HEADLINE> India Increases Defense Expenditure </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Presenting the 2000-01 budget in the Lok Sabha, the Lower House
of Indian Parliament, here on Tuesday, Finance Minister Yashwant
Sinha said more money would be provided for defense whenever
required.
</P>
<P>
This is the highest-ever increase in defense expenditure in any
single year in the country.
</P>
<P>
Sinha told the Parliament members that fiscal deficit in the
last fiscal year which will end on March 31 is likely to go up to
5.6 percent of the Gross Domestic Product (GDP) from the original
target of 4 percent.
</P>
<P>
The house has been in session since last Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
