<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Malaysia's Asset Management Company to Restructure  Loans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, February 29 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia's national asset
management company Danaharta is expected to restructure a total of
30 billion ringgit (7.894 billion U.S. dollars) in gross loans by
June this year, its managing director Azman Yahya said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Danaharta set up in June 1998 to acquire non-performing loans (
NPLs) completed its primary carve-out of NPLs on June 30, 1999,
and by December 31, 1999, it had taken over a total of 45.521
billion ringgit (11.979 billion U.S. dollars) in gross NPLs from
68 financial institutions, the director said while briefing
reporters on the company's operations for the six months ending
December 31, 1999.
</P>
<P>
According to Azman, as at the end of 1999, Danaharta had
restructured or disposed of loans and assets valued at 17.607
billion ringgit (4.633 billion U.S. dollars), representing 38
percent of loans in its portfolio.
</P>
<P>
He said Danaharta will conduct before end-March this year a
second property tender comprising 123 industrial, residential,
development, commercial, retail, agriculture and office properties
worth 276 million ringgit (72.631 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Danaharta managed to sell 24 properties worth 16.49 million
ringgit (4.339 million U.S. dollars) in its first tender of 44
properties worth 122.6 million ringgit (32.263 million U.S.
dollars) held last November, Azman said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he said Danaharta had completed the first sale by
restricted tender of foreign loans in August last year, involving
15 accounts worth 541.31 million ringgit (142.45 million U.S.
dollars) with a recovery rate of 55.3 percent on 13 accounts.
</P>
<P>
The second sale in December, involving 28 accounts worth 957
million ringgit (251.842 million U.S. dollars) has a recovery rate
of 71 percent on 25 accounts, he added.
</P>
<P>
He said that a total of 340 million U.S. dollars in foreign
currency loans were expected to be disposed of in the second
quarter of this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
