<HEADLINE> Uganda Announces Deadline for Party Petitions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, February 29 (Xinhua) -- Uganda Electoral Commission
(UEC) has announced March 7 as the deadline for receiving
verification and approval of any political system under the
Political System Act 2000.
</P>
<P>
A statement, made by UEC Chairman Aziz Kasujja, said on Tuesday
that all parties interested in presenting their petitions for
verification should do so not later than this date, Radio Uganda
reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Those not registered and approved by the commission would not
be qualified for participating the coming referendum. Uganda is
to hold a referendum in June to decide on the country's political
system.
</P>
<P>
The ruling National Resistance Movement and the multiparty
referendum committee have begun their campaign across the country
to lobby support so as to win in the referendum.
</P>
<P>
The UEC is responsible for organizing the referendum and
designing referendum questions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
