<HEADLINE> Eritreans in Ethiopia Ordered to Renew Residence Permits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, February 29 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia's Security,
Immigration and Refugee Affairs Authority (SIRAA) has ordered
Eritreans in the country to renew their residence permits for the
coming six months.
</P>
<P>
According to a SIRAA statement available Tuesday, the
registration of Eritreans living in Addis Ababa, the capital of
Ethiopia, is due to take place between February 28 and March 22 at
the Department of Immigration and Nationality.
</P>
<P>
Eritreans living outside the capital should appear in person
and register until April 8 either in the branch offices of the
authority or in the district police stations.
</P>
<P>
The statement warned that the authority will take the necessary
legal measures against those Eritreans who fail to renew their
residence permits.
</P>
<P>
There are estimated 150,000 to 200,000 Eritreans living in
Ethiopia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
