<DOCNO> XIE20000229.0171 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-02-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia Captures Last Populated Settlement in Chechnya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, February 29 (Xinhua) -- Russian troops have seized the
last populated settlement in Chenchnya, the Shatoi District Center,
60 kilometers south of the rebel republic's capital of Grozny in
the Argun gorge, said the Russian military Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
 The Itar-Tass news agency quoted the Russian Combined Forces'
headquarters in the North Caucasus as saying that Russian troops
Tuesday took full control of Shatoi, the last major rebel
stronghold in southern Chechnya, where some 2,000 Chechen rebels
had been resisting for the last days.
</P>
<P>
The Russian military said the seizure of strongly fortified
Shatoi was the key to controlling the last rebel-held areas in the
southern mountains.
</P>
<P>
The Russian Defense Ministry has confirmed that Russian
federal troops now fully control the town of Shatoi.
</P>
<P>
"Federal forces assumed full control of Shatoi on Tuesday
morning," the ministry's press service told press.
</P>
<P>
Russian presidential aide Sergei Yastrzhembsky also said that
Russian soldiers are in full control of Shatoi.
</P>
<P>
Russian federal troops marched into Shatoi at 5:00 p.m. Moscow
time (1400 GMT) on Monday, he said. The Russian flag will be
raised in Shatoi today.
</P>
<P>
A large amount of ammunition and equipment including the
militants' armored vehicles were seized in Shatoi, he said.
</P>
<P>
"A group of 200 militants had tried to leave Shatoi. Of these,
around 150 were killed," he said.
</P>
<P>
However, trench warfare is now still underway between Russian
federal forces and Chechen guerrillas in the Argun gorge area, the
news agency Interfax reported.
</P>
<P>
Russian federal units surrounded the strategically important
villages of Duba-Yurt, Dachu-Borzoi and Chishki in the valley over
the past 24 hours, the Russian command in the North Caucasus was
quoted as saying Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Wolf Gates mountain crossing to the Argun gorge has been
blocked off, while artillery and air strikes are continuing in the
gorge, it added.
</P>
<P>
Chechen extremists will probably try to break through the
Chechen section of the Russian-Georgian border. Around 500 federal
soldiers have been deployed in the area to reinforce the border
guard force, said the command.
</P>
<P>
Several days ago, the Russian Defense Ministry predicted that
99 percent of Chechen territories had been liberated by federal
troops after five months of the Russian anti-terrorist military
campaign in the rebellious province.
</P>
<P>
But Russian top military officials held that the seizure of
the Argun gorge will not end rebel resistance. They foresee hit-
and-run attacks by small rebel groups throughout Chechnya and warn
terrorist attacks in Russia are also possible. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000229.0172 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-02-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italian FM: No Reason for International Intervention in Chechnya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, February 28 (Xinhua) -- Italian Foreign Minister Lamberto
Dini said Monday that he believes there was no genocide in
Chechnya and no reason for international intervention in the
Russian republic.
</P>
<P>
 "You don't have the conditions you had in Kosovo, which
justified an intervention," he said in a radio interview.
</P>
<P>
"We are unfortunately facing a conflict by rebel forces who
are asking for autonomy, or even secession in Chechnya," he said.
</P>
<P>
"This is something that the Russian Federation is not ready to
concede," explained Dini, recalling the EU's various moves to urge
Russia to show moderation as well as its attempts to persuade
Russia to allow an international humanitarian presence.
</P>
<P>
"It is a conflict people tried to avoid, but unfortunately it
was impossible," said Dini, pointing out that Chechnya is Russian
territory and the Chechen rebel forces was considered as "
terrorists" by Moscow. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
