<HEADLINE> France's Unemployment Rate Continues to Drop  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The unemployment rate stood at 10.5 percent at the end of last
month, the lowest since 1992.
</P>
<P>
Compared with the same month in 1999, the number of jobless
people dropped by 11.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
Although the country's labor market has greatly improved, 2,654,
900 people in France are still seeking jobs, so it is too early to
toast champagne, the ministry said. 
</P>
