that his four predecessors agreed to give back all of the Golan
Heights, Barak's top aide Danny Yatom confirmed Monday that Yitzhak
Rabin did say he would be willing to cede the Golan.
</P>
<P>
Yatom served as the slain former premier's military adviser and
participated in the famous meeting between Rabin and then United
States Secretary of State Warren Christopher in 1993.
</P>
<P>
In the course of the meeting, Yatom said, Christopher asked
Rabin what he would be willing to offer if the Syrians gave him all
that he demanded regarding security and normalization. Rabin
confirmed he would not rule out the June 4, 1967 lines as one of
the borderlines the two countries would decide upon.
</P>
