return home, after failing to restart peace talks between Israel
and the Palestinians regarding a framework agreement for a final-
status peace deal.
</P>
<P>
In a meeting with Ross Monday morning, Palestinian leader Yasser
Arafat rejected Barak's compromise solution for renewing the talks.
</P>
<P>
Senior Palestinian officials said that Israel's compromise
proposal was for the Palestinians to choose an area making up 6.1
percent of the West Bank, but not including neighborhoods east of
Jerusalem, currently under Palestinian civilian authority and
Israeli security control. 
