<HEADLINE> Tanzania to Introduce Identity Cards in Western Regions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, February 29 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania is going to
introduce identity cards for Tanzanian citizens in the western
regions of the country where the influx of foreign refugees is
causing security problems, the Guardian newspaper reported on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
According to Kigoma Regional Commissioner Abubakar Mgumia,
identity cards will be issued in Kigoma, Kagera and Rukwa regions
within the next few months.
</P>
<P>
Mgumia said the IDs would also be useful in establishing
eligibility of voters during the general elections in October.
</P>
<P>
Scores of immigrant refugees who have entered the country
undeclared have taken part in civic elections whereby some have
even been elected as local government chairmen, he said.
</P>
<P>
Latest statistics from the United Nations High Commission for
Refugees show there are about 427,000 registered Burundian and
Congolese refugees staying in 13 camps in the western Kigoma and
Kagera regions. 
</P>
