<HEADLINE> Pedestrians Punished For Jaywalking in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, February 29 (Xinhua) -- Courts in Shanghai sentenced
two pedestrians who disobeyed traffic rules and beat up policemen.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Meizhen, a local resident, was fined ten yuan by a
traffic policeman when she jaywalked in November last year. She
slapped the policeman as she was trying to run away. Zhang was put
detained for four months.
</P>
<P>
Xia Zhengbiao, a farmer who works in Shanghai was sentenced to
six months in jail for crossing the road on a red light. He beat
up a traffic policeman who tried to detain him.
</P>
<P>
The violation of traffic rules by pedestrians and bicyclists is
a huge problem for policemen and transport authorities in Shanghai.
</P>
