<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ningxia Prepares for Development of Western China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, February 29 (Xinhua) -- Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region
in the northwest is speeding its work on a number of key
infrastructure projects as part of its concrete deeds to greet the
nationwide drive for accelerated economic growth in western China.
</P>
<P>
Mao Rubai, secretary of the Autonomous Regional Committee of
the Communist Party of China, made the remarks on the eve of the
third session of the Ninth National People's Congress (NPC), which
is due to open on March 5.
</P>
<P>
Mao, who is also a deputy to the Third Session of the Ninth NPC,
said today that the autonomous region's investment in fixed assets
will be risen to 15 billion yuan (1.8 billion US dollars) this
year, equivalent to the combined sum of the past two years. The
figure is to spiral in upcoming years.
</P>
<P>
Major construction projects, now under way in his region,
include a railway section from Yinchuan, the regional capital, to
Taiyuan, capital of north China's Shanxi Province, a new air route,
a number of water control and irrigation extension projects, and a
highway network, he said.
</P>
<P>
Ningxia, located on the upper and middle reaches of the Yellow
River, China's second longest, is frequented by wind and sand
storms. Therefore, the autonomous region plans to plant more trees
and grass on more than one million ha of land over the next decade.
When the afforestation target is met, additional 12,000 sq km of
fields with serious erosion will be improved. And its forest
coverage rate will increase to 13 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
