<HEADLINE> Share Prices End Mixed in Tokyo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, February 29 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices closed mixed in
Tokyo Tuesday, with high-tech blue chips remaining firm while high-
priced information and telecom issues moving down.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange rose 239.42 points, or 1.21
percent from Monday's close to end at 19,959.52.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX) which covers
all First Section issues, however, marked its first downturn in
five trading days, losing 9.50 points or 0.55 percent to 1,718.94.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the major section increased to 710.29 million
shares from Monday's 656.45 million.
</P>
<P>
Mitsubishi Electric was the day's volume leader.
</P>
<P>
Export-oriented technology issues gained ground after the Dow
Jones Industrial Average in New York recovered to the 10,000 level
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. dollar's rebound to the 110 yen range also made
investors feel good about buying these exporters, traders said.
</P>
<P>
Telecom-related issues turned downward following their recent
gain.
</P>
<P>
Advancers included pharmaceutical firms, rubber makers and oil
distributors while paper manufacturers, automakers and
construction firms were among losers.
</P>
<P>
Of the issues listed on the First Section, gainers outpaced
losers 735 to 521, with 104 issues closing unchanged. 
</P>
</TEXT>
