<HEADLINE> China's Coastal City Attracts Overseas Tourists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, February 29 (Xinhua) -- Quanzhou, a coastal city in
east China's Fujian Province and the famous hometown of many
overseas Chinese, has become a major tourist destination.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics show the city hosted more than 9.2 million
domestic and overseas tourists last year, including 420,000 from
abroad.
</P>
<P>
Quanzhou boasts some 400 historical and cultural sites, such as
Kaiyuan Temple and Xuefeng Temple. It is also the birthplace of a
variety of artistic forms like Nanyin, a major Chinese folk music
form performed by string and wind instruments such as pipa, a
plucked string instrument, and Dongxiao, a vertical bamboo flute.
</P>
<P>
Over the past decade, the city has restored about 60 historical
sites and made them open to tourists.
</P>
<P>
A great number of museums, including an overseas transportation
museum, and a museum of the history of overseas Chinese have been
established.
</P>
<P>
The city has also staged a series of international events like
a Nanyin concert and a folk art festival to draw overseas tourists.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
