<HEADLINE> China to Host 2001 World Archery Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 29 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese capital Beijing
will host the 41st World Archery Championships next year,
officials from China's archery authorities announced here on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Gao Zhidan, Vice Director of the Administrative Center for
Shooting and Archery, told a conference that he estimated there
will be about 600 archers from 50 to 60 countries and regions
competing at the championships. The championships will open on
September 11, 2001 and conclude on September 21.
</P>
<P>
He said that the eight events at the biennial championships
will be held on a 25,000-square-meter range in suburban Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The range, which has hosted the Asian Games, Asian Cup and
Asian Championships archery competitions, will undergo a
renovation to meet FITA requirements for the world championships.
</P>
<P>
China boasts 300 archery clubs and 100 amateur sports schools
which include archery training. The national squad grabbed a women
's team silver medal at last year's world championships. 
</P>
