<HEADLINE> Kingdom of Tobacco Cuts Cigarette Export to Stabilize Price </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, February 29 (Xinhua) -- Yunnan, a leading tobacco
producer of China, cut its cigarette export by 173 million U.S.
dollars last year in a bid to stabilize price.
</P>
<P>
The province's cigarette export was down 60 percentage points
compared with the previous year.
</P>
<P>
As a result, the total export of the province was also down 8.5
percentage points in 1999, according to statistics from the
provincial foreign trade and economic cooperation department.
</P>
<P>
The reduced cigarette export was aimed at stabilizing cigarette
price and maintaining domestic market order.
</P>
<P>
Many of China's famous brands of cigarette are produced by
Yunnan, known as the "kingdom of tobacco". However, a large
quantity of exported cigarettes by Yunnan were returned to China
by overseas profiteers through illegal channels, disturbing
domestic market order.
</P>
<P>
Yunnan has produced about one third of China's cigarettes since
the 1980s, with 70 percent of Yunnan's revenue coming from the
tobacco industry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
