<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam to Export 1.68 Bln U.S. Dollars of Goods to Japan This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, February 29 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam is striving to export 1.
68 billion U.S. dollars worth of goods to Japan this year, equal
to last year's figure and an increase of 25 percent over 1998,
English daily Vietnam News reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Japan is a major export market for Vietnamese products.
</P>
<P>
From 1991 to 1997, bilateral trade between Vietnam and Japan
increased steadily. Vietnam's exports to Japan accounted for 25
percent to 28 percent of its total annual exports.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam now ranks the 20th on the list of the 120 countries
exporting marine products to Japan.
</P>
<P>
However, Vietnamese trade officials said that Vietnam's exports
have not yet reached their full potential and do not yet meet the
requirements of the Japanese market in terms of quality.
</P>
<P>
About half of Vietnam's main exports to Japan are raw materials
or semi-processed goods.
</P>
<P>
But Japan's imports from Vietnam represent just 0.6 percent of
its total annual imports. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000229.0261 </DOCNO>
