<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, February 29 (Xinhua) -- The fourth race of the
America's Cup finals series was postponed Tuesday because of a
lack of wind on the Hauraki Gulf off Auckland, the largest city of
New Zealand.
</P>
<P>
The wind failed to build past four knots in the afternoon,
forcing the crews of Team New Zealand and Prada of Italy into a
long wait out on the course.
</P>
