<HEADLINE> Shanghai to Set up New Industry Zone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, February 29 (Xinhua) -- The municipal government of
Shanghai has decided to build a comprehensive industry zone, with
focus on high technology, in the southern part of the city.
</P>
<P>
The zone will be established on the basis of the 20-square
meter Fengpu Industrial Zone in Fengxian County, according to the
decision made on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Industry Investment Group and Fengxian County
government will make an investment of 200 million yuan (about 24
million U.S. dollars) to set up a company for the planning,
development, land lease and infrastructure construction, as well
as attracting of investments in the zone.
</P>
<P>
The zone is the third in Shanghai, China's largest industrial
and commercial center, following the Zhangjiang High-tech Park and
Caojing Chemical Industry Zone.  
