<HEADLINE> Sichuan to Publish Air Quality Report in 13 Cities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, February 29 (Xinhua) -- In a fresh move to intensify
its environment protection effort, Sichuan Province in southwest
China has decided to publish a weekly report on air quality in 13
major cities before the upcoming "World Environment Day" which
falls on June 5.
</P>
<P>
Air quality monitoring systems have now been put into trial
operations in these cities and related data will be submitted to
the provincial environmental protection department to form the
basis of the weekly report.
</P>
<P>
The 13 cities include Panzhihua, Mianyang, Guangyuan, Luzhou,
Leshan, Yibin and seven other cities.
</P>
<P>
The province has also planned to monitor water quality and
major sources of pollution in some cities on a regular basis.
