<HEADLINE> Xinjiang Builds Eight State Garners </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, February 29 (Xinhua) -- Work on eight garners for state
grain reserves has been completed in northwest China's Xinjiang
Uygur Autonomous Region, one of China's leading grain production
bases.
</P>
<P>
The first batch of grain has been put into the warehouses,
solving a long-standing headache of farmers who found it difficult
to sell their grain to the state as a result of shortage of
storage space, said a local official.
</P>
<P>
The eight granaries, with a combined storage capacity of 550
million km, were built in Hami, Korla, Aksu, Kuytun, Shihezi,
Fukang, Jinghe and Qingshuihe counties, respectively.
</P>
<P>
Construction of these projects took seven months and cost a
total of 3.2 billion yuan appropriated by the central government.
