<HEADLINE> Panzhihua Aims to Become Tourist City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANZHIHUA (Sichuan), February 29 (Xinhua) -- Panzhihua, known
as the "city of sunshine" in southwest China's Sichuan Province,
is working to build itself into a tourist city in the next 10
years.
</P>
<P>
Mayor Zhang Chengming told Xinhua in an interview that the city
bases this ambitious plan on its rich natural resources and good
conditions for developing tourism.
</P>
<P>
Last year, 820,000 domestic and overseas tourists visited the
city, bringing a total tourism income of 440 million yuan, Zhang
said.
</P>
<P>
The city's Ertan Hydropower Station, the largest of its kind in
operation in China, and the Panzhihua Iron and Steel Company have
become tourist destinations, said Fei Qi, deputy director of the
city's tourism bureau. He added the two places have received tens
of thousands of domestic and overseas tourists.
</P>
<P>
With an annual average temperature of 18.5 degrees Celsius, the
city, which is also the country's largest energy, iron, steel,
vanadium and titanium production base in southwestern area, has
unique local customs, cultural relics and diversified biological
resources.
</P>
<P>
As an important communication hub linking Sichuan and Yunnan
provinces, Panzhihua is a major stopover for tourists to go to
Chengdu, the provincial capital of Sichuan and the tourist cities
of Dali and Lijiang in Yunnan.
</P>
<P>
The mayor said that the cental government strategy to develop
the western regions of China would help improve the city's
infrastructure facilities to further upgrade local tourist
industry.  
</P>
</TEXT>
