<HEADLINE> Chongqing Sees Growing Overseas Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, February 29 (Xinhua)-- The actual use of overseas
investment in China's largest municipality of Chongqing last year
was reported at 241 million U.S. dollars, 3.61 percent higher than
in 1998.
</P>
<P>
Based on a year-on-year 11 percent increase of overseas direct
investment here in 1998 over 1997, some 197 new projects were set
up last year with total contractual overseas investment of 510
million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Of the 197 new projects, 25 involve over ten million U.S.
dollars each, with investment in each project averaging three
million U.S. dollars, up 40 percent than that in 1998.
</P>
<P>
Major investors came from the United States and European
nations. Nearly 20 nations established some 36 enterprises,
chalking a total contractual investment of 140 million U.S.
dollars, up 50 percent than 1998.
</P>
<P>
The growth of overseas investments was propelled by the local
preferential policies introduced since Chongqing was named a
municipality directly under the central authorities in 1997.
</P>
