<HEADLINE> Ostertag Fined $7,500, Smith $3,000 for Altercation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
WASHINGTON, February 28 (Xinhua) -- Utah Jazz center Greg
Ostertag and Portland Trail Blazers guard Steve Smith Monday were
fined $7,500 and $3,000 respectively, for their roles in an
altercation during a game on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
With 5:12 to play in Portland's 101-92 win, Ostertag became
entangled with Smith in a battle for a loose ball. Ostertag locked
Smith's right arm under his left arm and did not let go, prompting
a shoving match.
</P>
<P>
Ostertag began taking swipes at Smith before being ejected. He
received the heavier fine for booting a basketball into the upper
deck of the Rose Garden before storming off the court.
</P>
<P>
"I just got locked up," he said. "I asked Smith if he was all
right and he got upset. This is a heated rivalry when we play at
home or away. Both teams play hard, trying to get a win. This
stuff happens." 
</P>
