<HEADLINE> Norwegian Skiers Impressive at World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, February 28 (Xinhua) -- Norwegians won both men's
and women's World Cup cross-country sprint ski races on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Under the unpopular knockout format, reigning overall champion
Bente Martinsen used a strong kick to beat Finland's Pirjo
Manninen in the women's final set around Stockholm's 18th century
Royal Palace.
</P>
<P>
Odd-Bjorn Hjelmeset easily outpaced team mate Tore Bjonviken in
the men's final.
</P>
<P>
Kati Sundqvist of Finland scored a upset third-place win over
Russia's Larissa Lazutina, second in the standings.
</P>
<P>
Havard Solbakken finished third in a Norwegian men's sweep of
the podium by eliminating compatriot Tore Arne Hetland. 
