<HEADLINE> FIFA Praise Highly Morocco's World Cup Bid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, February 28 (Xinhua) -- Morocco's bid to host the 2006
World Cup finals was "very, very impressive", FIFA officials said
at the end of a five-day inspection.
</P>
<P>
"We were impressed by the official commitment to organise the
cup. The feeling is something we are very interested in," Alan
Rothenberg, head of FIFA's inspection team, was quoted as saying
on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The team toured several cities to inspect stadiums, security,
roads, telecommunications and hotel facilities, reports reaching
here said.
</P>
<P>
Morocco, whose bids were failed to stage the 1994 and 1998
finals, are campaigning against England, Germany, South Africa,
and Brazil to host the 2006 tournament.
</P>
<P>
FIFA's 24-member executive committee will make the final
decision In Zurich on July 5 and 6. 
</P>
