<HEADLINE> HK Holds Olympics Table Tennis Asian Qualifying Tournament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A total of 108 competitors from 20 Asian countries and regions
will vie for 11 men's singles and women's singles berths and six
men's and women's doubles berths respectively.
</P>
<P>
The six-day tournament features four events -- men's singles,
women's singles, men's doubles and women's doubles, which are
played on a round robin format.
</P>
<P>
The top 20 men players and the top 20 women's players in the
ITTF world rankings just after the individual events of the 45th
world championships last year, have secured their berths
automatically for the singles events in the Sydney Olympics.
</P>
<P>
All the other players wishing to participate in the singles and
doubles events must take part in their own continental qualifying
in order to obtain a berth into the Olympics. 
</P>
</TEXT>
