<HEADLINE> Iranian President: Israel Never Wants Real Peace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, February 29 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Mohammad
Khatami said on Tuesday that Israel had never wanted real peace in
the Middle East region.
</P>
<P>
"Regular attacks by Israel on Lebanon and elsewhere are
sufficient proof of the disinclination of the Zionist regime to
peace," Khatami said while meeting with visiting Lebanese
Parliament Speaker Nabih Berri.
</P>
<P>
Khatami was quoted by the official Islamic Republic News Agency
(IRNA) as stressing that under the current circumstances, it is
extremely important that Arab and Muslim nations share the same
feelings and policies in confronting the "Zionist atrocity."
</P>
<P>
Muslim nations need to better understand the hard realities both
regionally and internationally for their own prosperity and
progress, Khatami told the Lebanese official, who is in Tehran to
attend an extraordinary meeting of the inter-parliamentary session
of the Organization of the Islamic Conference, which opened on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
Berri extended his thanks for Iran's support for the cause of
Lebanon's resistance against Israeli occupation.
</P>
<P>
Israeli set up a self-styled security zone in south Lebanon in
1985 with a claimed aim of protecting its north from cross-border
guerrilla attacks.
</P>
<P>
Since then, the Iranian-backed Hezbollah, or Party of God, has
been spearheading a guerrilla war to oust Israeli troops and its
ally South Lebanon Army from the country.
</P>
<P>
Berri also conveyed an invitation from Lebanese President Emile
Lahoud for Khatami to visit Beirut. Khatami accepted the
invitation, IRNA said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
