police commanders and personnel of attacking student dorms and
beating students, the Islamic Republic News Agency reported. (Iran-
Trial)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY -- Sheikh Hamad Bin Jassem, cousin of the Qatari
emir and former economy and trade minister, was sentenced to life
imprisonment by Qatar's Supreme Criminal Court on Tuesday for
masterminding the 1996 coup attempt.
</P>
<P>
Some 32 of his supporters were also given life sentences for the
foiled bid to overthrow Emir Sheikh Hamad Bin Khalifa al-Thani, the
Kuwait News Agency reported from Doha, capital of Qatar.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the three-judge panel acquitted 85 others of the 118
defendants accused of involvement in the foiled coup on February
13, 1996. (Qatar-Coup-Trial)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iran on Tuesday reiterated its support for Lebanon's
independence, territorial integrity and national unity as well as
the Lebanese resistance movement fighting against Israeli
occupation.
</P>
<P>
Iranian Majlis (Parliament) Speaker Ali Akbar Nateq Nouri and
former President Hashemi Rafsanjani all made clear Tehran's stance
during their separate meetings with visiting President of the
Lebanese National Assembly Nabin Berri.
</P>
<P>
Nouri said that solidarity and cohesion among the Lebanese
nation and the brave stances taken by Lebanese officials in support
of Lebanese resistance movement against the Israeli expansionist
policies are the sole way of repelling Israeli aggression. (Iran-
Lebanon-Support)
</P>
<P>
