</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak has full
confidence in Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak's intention on
peace, an Egyptian envoy said here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Osama el-Baz, Mubarak's political adviser, stressed during his
meeting with Barak that Mubarak believed Barak is determined to
move forward the peace process with the Arabs, a statement released
by Barak's office said.
</P>
<P>
Barak briefed el-Baz on the current deadlocks in the peace
process with Syria and the Palestinians, and promised to seize all
chances to advance on both peace tracks. (Israel-Egypt-Relations)
</P>
