<HEADLINE> 6-Year-Old Girl Shot Dead in U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The shooting happened at about 10 a.m. local time at Buell
Elementary School north of Flint in the state.
</P>
<P>
The injured pupil was taken to a nearby hospital, and was
pronounced dead half an hour later.
</P>
<P>
This was the latest in a series of shootings to hit American
schools.
</P>
<P>
It was not immediately clear if the shooting was accidental or
intentional, but Genesee County Prosecutor Arthur Busch said
authorities were investigating reports that a playground fight
preceded the shooting.
</P>
<P>
There were no other injuries. Only one shot was fired, said
police, who took the suspected shooter into custody.
</P>
<P>
It was not clear how the gun was brought into the school and
police did not name the shooter or the victim.
</P>
<P>
Some 22 pupils were in the classroom at the time of the
shooting. Police evacuated the rest of the school, but detained
the pupils who were in the class for counselling and further
questioning. 
