<HEADLINE> Congress Urged to Grant China PNTR </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"In the most basic sense, when we consider China's WTO and
permanent Normal Trade Relations, we are facing a clear choice,"
said at a luncheon hosted by the Asian Society.
</P>
<P>
"China is the world's largest country, and over the past
decade the world's fastest-growing major economy. The future
course of our relationship will have great bearing on American
security and strategy in the 21st strategy," she added.
</P>
<P>
She also holds that China's accession to the WTO and PNTR
would go far beyond trade and economic benefit to enhance China's
reforms and improve its human rights records.
</P>
<P>
