<HEADLINE> Colombian Armed Group Kill Eight People </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bogota, February 29 (Xinhua) -- A group of 15 armed men have
assassinate eight people in El Tigre farm, district of Casanare,
east of Colombia, police sources said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
All victims were taken out of their homes by force Monday
night and then killed, police sources said, adding that such
massacre was made by the paramilitary group of Colombian United
Auto-defense fighting in that zone.
</P>
<P>
Five of the assassinated people were part of the Feliciano
family, the farm's owners and the other three were workers.
</P>
<P>
One hundred people have been killed by paramilitary groups in
the last two weeks, blaming them of collaborating with the
Colombian guerrilla.
</P>
<P>
Outlawed paramilitary forces, numbering up to 7,000 members
nationwide, have killed leftists and suspected rebel sympathizers
across Colombia for more than a decade. Human rights groups have
long blamed their secret, dirty war, for an overwhelming majority
of the peasant massacres and other atrocities committed INA
conflict that has taken more than 35,000 lives in the last decade.
</P>
</TEXT>
