<DATE_TIME> 2000-02-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Switzerland, Albania Sign Accord on Refugee Repatriation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, February 29 (Xinhua) -- Switzerland and Albania have
signed an accord on the repatriation of asylum-seekers from
Albania and refugees from Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
According to the deal signed in Berne Tuesday by visiting
Albanian Justice Minister Spartak Poci and his Swiss counterpart
Ruth Metzler,refugees whose requests for asylum have been turned
down will have to return to Albania. It also allows Berne to send
Kosovo Albanians home via Albania.
</P>
<P>
About 50,000 people who were given temporary shelter in
Switzerland during last year's conflict are due to be "forcibly"
repatriated if they have not returned to Kosovo by the end of May,
said Swiss Radio International.
</P>
<P>
Currently, most refugees are repatriated to Kosovo by air to
Pristina, but the accord will make it possible for Kosovars to go
home overland. The deal was drafted in January, during a visit to
Albania by the Swiss justice minister. 
</P>
</TEXT>
