<HEADLINE> Zambia Urges for Improvement of Water Resources Management </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, February 29 (Xinhua) -- The Zambian government has
called for the people to target the problems and challenges facing
the water resource management sector in the country.
</P>
<P>
The call was contained in a statement released at the country's
first Water and Sanitation National Workshop titled "Challenges of
Managing Sustainable Water and Sanitation in the 21st Century in
Zambia" held here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In the statement, the government stressed the need for the
public, private sector, non-governmental organizations and all
other partners in the water and sanitation sector to join hands in
addressing the challenges facing the country.
</P>
<P>
Zambia, and the region as a whole, faces enormous demands on
water resources with the population growing rapidly, the statement
said.
</P>
<P>
It said that this problem cannot be addressed by the government
alone, noting that it is for this reason that the government has
welcomed the establishment of the Water and Sanitation Association
of Zambia (WASAZA) at the workshop.
</P>
<P>
Being a corporate member of the Eastern and Southern African
Region Chapter of the International Water Association, WASAZA aims
to assist in the development of professional competence and the
best practical performance standards for water and sanitation
management at both national and regional levels.
</P>
<P>
It also aims to provide a forum through which all matters
relating to the management of water and sanitation can be
integrated through interdisciplinary discussions and agreements.
</P>
</TEXT>
