<P>
He was received by Mozambican Prime Minister Pascoal Mocumbi,
who briefed him on the problems caused by the floods and the
equipment needed for relief operations.
</P>
<P>
After the meeting, Lekota, together with his Mozambican
counterpart Tobias Dai, boarded a South African air force
helicopter to overfly the areas worst hit by the floods.
</P>
<P>
The Mozambican government has requested additional air support
from South Africa, and Pretoria has promised a further two
helicopters.
</P>
<P>
This is in addition to five South African helicopters and two
light aircraft already working in the flood zones.
</P>
<P>
It is expected that the South African government will increase
its commitment to Mozambique's flood relief efforts following
Lekota's visit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
