<HEADLINE> Zambian Government Debt Rises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, February 29 (Xinhua) -- The Zambian government's debt
owed to the banks has increased to 878.9 billion kwacha (321
million U.S. dollars) from 695.6 billion kwacha (253 million U.S.
dollars) in December, according to Financial Mail on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The increasing government debt raises concern in the private
sector and monetary authorities because it leaves less credit for
the private sector for investment or expansion which in turn
creates jobs.
</P>
<P>
The increased borrowing by the government also pushes up the
interest rates because the government has to offer higher
interests to attract the banks to buy its treasury bonds. 
