<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 4,792 Nigerians Arrested for Drug-related Offense </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, February 29 (Xinhua) -- The Nigerian National Drug Law
Enforcement Agency arrested 4,792 Nigerians for drug-related
offense in 1999, a government official said.
</P>
<P>
Ogbonna Onovo, chairman of the anti-drug agency, told a press
conference Monday that 2,291 suspects were arrested with marijuana
at the country's sea and air ports alone.
</P>
<P>
As a result of a reinforced anti-drug trafficking exercise, a
total of 18,120 kilograms of drugs, among which about 98 percent
were "cannabis sativa", a locally grown and processed substance,
were seized last year, Onovo said.
</P>
<P>
The anti-drug official condemned the increasing use of
teenagers by drug farm merchants inside the country's thick
forests and warned that sterner measures will henceforth be taken
against the farmers.
</P>
<P>
The wicked farmers lured unsuspecting teenagers into the thick
forests to work for them with promises of generous incentives,
because these juveniles are not within the age range of those can
be prosecuted, Onovo added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
